specialization of iterator concepts.

entry.title: Move layer destruction out of Canvas2DLayerBridge
entry.content:
https://crrev.com/c/4881264 moved the cc:TextureLayer from

Canvas2DLayerBridge to CanvasResourceHost. The Canvas2DLayerBridge

destructor was originally deleting the layer, but it was updated to

call resource_host_->ResetLayer(). This call however was not

executing when disabling acceleration because

ReplaceExisting2dLayerBridge clears

Canvas2DLayerBridge::resource_host_ before deleting the

Canvas2DLayerBridge objects.



This resulted in the CanvasResourceHost having a layer but no

resource provider. In that state,

Canvas2DLayerBridge::GetOrCreateResourceProvider refuses to re-create

the provider as it assumes the context should be restored instead:

https://crsrc.org/c/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/canvas_2d_layer_bridge.cc;l=215;drc=47781acaec132d6d3cbd52feea008925e4e88f67



This fix brings back the original behavior of deleting the layer when

the bridge is destroyed.

function replace {

| uniq \

| grep \

entry.title: Ownership: Implement migration to hardware-backed keys
entry.content:
Implement the migration of owner keys from the public slot to the

private slot, which is hardware-backed. The migration is split into

two stages: 1) generating new keys in the private slot, 2) moving

all the existing keys.

Add new feature flags to control the migration: StoreOwnerKeyInPrivateSlot and MigrateOwnerKeyToPrivateSlot.

They will be enabled later.



Behavior of the feature flag combinations:

Features | Behavior

Store | Migrate | New key | Existing key

----------+-----------+--------------+----------------------

0 | 0 | public slot | migrate to public slot

0 | 1 | public slot | migrate to public slot

1 | 0 | private slot | keep wherever it is

1 | 1 | private slot | migrate to private slot



Also add more counters to the OwnerKeyUmaEvent UMA histogram and

postpone its expiration date.



Bug: b/264397430

entry.title: Reland "[display] Propagate change state on display config update"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit 11e791d0b2c6d2bbbd1fd43345a64aaf320b49cb



See diff against patchset 1. Missing a reset() in the test

fixture's TearDown() method.



Original change's description:

> [display] Propagate change state on display config update

>

> This CL updates OnDidProcessDisplayChanges() to propagate a struct

> of changes to the display configuration. This API is currently only

> implemented by ChromeOS Ash.

>

> There are several DisplayManager methods that modify the existing

> display configuration and these methods can call each other in a

> nested fashion. BeginEndNotifier exists to allow a single call to

> OnWillProcessDisplayChanges() and OnDidProcessDisplayChanges() on

> either side of an atomic change in display configuration state.

>

> This CL introduces DisplayManager::PendingDisplayChanges which is

> intended to track all display config changes that occur before

> the last BeginEndNotifier falls out of scope. At this time

> this is translated to a DisplayConfigurationChange struct more

> appropriate for observers and propagated in the call to

> OnDidProcessDisplayChanges().

>

> This CL also adds a test to ensure what is propagated by

> the DisplayManagerObserver is consistent with what is propagated by

> the DisplayObserver.

>

> Follow up CLs will also

> - update exo to leverage this as a means to consume an atomic

> update to the display configuration state.

>

> - consolidate the other existing mechanisms that communicate

> display configuration changes. For e.g. see

> DisplayManager::Delegate::Pre[Post]DisplayConfigurationChange()

> and downstream methods.

>

> - update clients that rely on other means to infer display

> configuration changes (using OnDisplayAdded[Removed]() for e.g.)

entry.title: NavigationPredictor: Only store hashes of seen URLs to save memory
entry.content:
NavigationPredictor stores a set of all the URLs it has processed to

avoid sending duplicate predictions to the prediction service. This

could grow quite large for a page with many links. Since we only need to

test whether a new URL is in the set, we can hash the URLs instead of

storing the entire URL.



For example, when loading the single page HTML spec, the size in bytes

of this set goes from 77,852 currently to 15,800 with this CL.

entry.title: cc/metrics: AddSortedFrame for trackers pending removal
entry.content:
FrameSequenceTracker and FrameSequenceMetrics do the frame counting

and metrics reported in AddSortedFrame for v3. FrameSorter could

defer AddSortedFrame when frames are out of order. AddSortedFrame

are not called for trackers that are scheduled for termination and

pending removal. This is a problem for short UI animations which

is usually 150ms (about 10 frames). If a frame at start is finished

later, AddSortedFrame would not happen and no metrics are reported

This CL fixes the issue by calling AddSortedFrame for pending

removal trackers as well.



And re-enable disabled overview/splitview tests in ash_unittests.

entry.title: Remove state from Android accessibility tree manager and nodes
entry.content:
This CL removes some state kept in the C++ Android accessibility code

and points the code to AccessibilityState instead.



Prior to this CL, the user settings for whether or not to expose the

characters of a password were stored in AccessibilityState, and they

were duplicated into web_contents_accessibility_android. When a node

needed to know the setting, it called through its root manager to

wcax to get the setting. This ties the state to a specific manager and

web contents, which is not ideal.



With this CL we remove these code paths and instead point a node

directly to the AccessibilityState by means of a call to a static JNI

method in accessibility_state.cc. This keeps the same logic, and uses

the same underlying methods, but removes the duplicate state storage

from the manager and wcax, and points nodes directly to the source of

truth for the state.
